Learn:
We’ll analyze the text via several steps.
| [[Literal]] | [[Basic ]] | [[Comprehend]] | [[Analyze]] |

Literal: 
*Literal (1/12):* Let’s make a literal translation of each word of the Gemara.
< גמ‘ השתא בשלוחו מקדש בו מיבעיא <gray>אמר
< רב יוסף מצוה בו יותר מבשלוחו כי הא דרב</gray>
> *‘גמ* – ‎גְּמָרָא – _Gemara_ (from printer, marking end of Mishnah and start of Gemara) <small>{{[[גמ‘|→]]}}</small>
> *הַשְׁתָּא* – _hashta_ – Now <small>{{[[השתא|→]]}}</small>
> *בִּשְׁלוּחוֹ* – _b’shlucho_ – in/on/with, his shaliach <small>{{[[בשלוחו|→]]}}</small>
> *מְקַדֵּשׁ* – _mekadesh_ – he/it, is/is being, _mekadesh_[^(1)] <small>{{[[מקדש|→]]}}</small>
> *בּוֹ* – _bo_ – in/on/with, himself <small>{{[[בו|→]]}}</small>
> *מִיבָּעֵיא* – _meboya_ – needed <small>{{[[מיבעיא|→]]}}</small>
1) We said earlier מקדש, _mekadesh_, is a word that general means one male is doing something to increase holiness, such as saying _kiddush_, designating a day as a festival, or designating a woman for marriage via the initial _kiddushin_ stage.
===
> [[Literal 2|Next]]
> [[#Basic]]
===

Literal 2:
*Literal (2/12):* Let’s continue our literal translation of the Gemara.
< <gray>גמ’ השתא בשלוחו מקדש בו מיבעיא</gray> אמר
< רב יוסף מצוה בו יותר מבשלוחו <gray> כי הא דרב</gray>
> *אָמַר* – _amar_ – said <small>{{[[אמר|→]]}}</small>
> *רַב* – Rav <small>{{[[רב|→]]}}</small>
> *יוֹסֵף* – Yosef <small>{{[[יוסף|→]]}}</small>
> *מִצְוָה* – _mitzvah_ <small>{{[[מצוה|→]]}}</small>
> *בּוֹ* – in/on/with, himself <small>{{[[בו|→]]}}</small>
> *יוֹתֵר* – _yoser_ – more <small>{{[[יותר|→]]}}</small>
> *מִבִּשְׁלוּחוֹ* – _m’b’shlucho_ – from/than, in/on/with, his/its _shaliach_ <small>{{[[מבשלוחו|→]]}}</small>
===
> [[Literal 3|Next]]
> [[#Basic]]
===

Literal 3:
*Literal (3/12):* Let’s continue our literal translation of the Gemara.
< <gray>גמ’ השתא בשלוחו מקדש בו מיבעיא אמר
< רב יוסף מצוה בו יותר מבשלוחו  </gray>כי הא דרב
< ספרא מחריך רישא רבא מלח שיבוטא<gray>
< איכא דאמרי בהא איסורא נמי אית בה</gray>
> *כִּי* – ki – because/if/as/like <small>{{[[כי|→]]}}</small>
> *הָא* – _ha_ – this/that <small>{{[[הא|→]]}}</small>
> *דְּרַב* – _d’Rav_ – of Rav <small>{{[[דרב|→]]}}</small>
> *סַפְרָא* – _Safra_ <small>{{[[ספרא|→]]}}</small>
> *מַחְרִיךְ* – _machrich_ – [someone] burned/singed [something] <small>{{[[מחריך|→]]}}</small>
> *רֵישָׁא* – _reisha_ – the head/top/beginning <small>{{[[רישא|→]]}}</small>
> *רָבָא* – _Rava_ <small>{{[[רבא|→]]}}</small>
> *מָלַח* – _malach_ – salted <small>{{[[מלח|→]]}}</small>
> *שִׁיבּוּטָא* – _shibuta_ <small>{{[[שיבוטא|→]]}}</small>
The word שיבוטא _shibuta_ doesn’t seem to have been as widely used as the other words here because we find later authorities giving definitions for it, so it may not have a common literal translation.
===
> [[Literal 4|Next]]
> [[#Basic]]
