> *אָסוּר* – _asur_ – [is] prohibited <small>{{[[אסור|→]]}}</small>
> *לְאָדָם* – _l’adam_ – to man/a man <small>{{[[לאדם|→]]}}</small>
> *שֶׁיְּקַדֵּשׁ* – _sh’yekadesh_ – that he will be _mekadesh_ <small>{{[[שיקדש|→]]}}</small>
> *אֶת* – _es_ – [tells you the previous verb is being done to the following word]  <small>{{[[את|→]]}}</small> 
> *הָאִשָּׁה* – _ha’isha_ – the woman <small>{{[[האשה|→]]}}</small>
> *עַד* – _ad_ – until <small>{{[[עד|→]]}}</small>
> *שֶׁיְּרֶאֶנָּה* – _sh’yerena_ – that he will see her/it <small>{{[[שיראנה|→]]}}</small>
