> [[^]]
===


* אתמר:


* בַּת: The Hebrew word בַּת means “daughter.”
- It can appear with posessive suffixes such as [[בתו|בִּתּוֹ]] (_bito_, “his daughter.”)


* באנפא:


* בבות:


* בבתו:


* בגדולה:


* בגמ’: This is an abbreviation for בַּגְּמָרָא, “in the Gemara.”


* בדידה:


* בדידיה:


* בה:
The letters בה are probably the prefix ב being used to refer to a feminine entity:
- The prefix ב has various meanings including “in” and “with.” <small>{{[[Prefix ב#Meanings|→]]}}</small>
- When followed by the suffix ה‎, the ב can be referencing “her” or “it.” <small>{{[[Prefix ב#בָּהּ|→]]}}</small>
- So, בה can mean “in her/it,” “with her/it,” “on her/it,” “regarding her/it,” or any other combination.
(There is a word that sounds like _“ba”_ that means “comes” or “came” but that’s spelled בָּא not בַּהּ.)

The letters בה are probably the [[Prefix ב#Various suffixes|the prefix ב with the feminine singular suffix]].
- The prefix ב has [[Prefix ב#Meanings|various meanings]] including “in” and “with.”


* בהא: The letters בהא could be:
- The [[prefix ב]] meaning in/on/with/regarding etc. <small>{{[[Prefix ב#Meanings|→]]}}</small>
- The Aramaic word [[הָא]] meaning “this” or “that.”


* בו:
The letters בו are probably the [[Prefix ב#suffixes|the prefix ב]] when referring to something masculine:
- The prefix ב has various meanings including “in” and “with.” <small>{{[[Prefix ב#Meanings|→]]}}</small>
- When followed by the suffix ו, the ב can be referencing “him” or “it.” <small>{{[[Prefix ב#בּוֹ|→]]}}</small>
- So, בו can mean “in her/it,” “with him/it,” “on him/it,” “regarding him/it,” or any other combination.
(There is a word that sounds like “bo” that means “come” but that’s spelled בּוֹא not בּוֹ.)


* ביד:


* בידו:


* בין:


* ביתו:


* בלא:


* בלאו:


* במצוה:


* במצות:


* במתני:


* בנותינו:


* בסיפא:


